on Hudud: Punishment of theft suspended during famine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Yahya ibn Abi Kathir reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThe hand of the thief is not cut who steals a bundle of dates or in a year of famine.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Abd al-Razza\u0304q 18371 Al-Sa\u2019di reported: I asked Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah have\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5692,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/30\/haram-cut-animals-alive\/","url_meta":{"origin":13531,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Animals: Cutting animals while alive is forbidden","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 30, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Waqid al-Layth reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhatever is cut from an animal while it is alive is unlawful carrion.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"This is acted upon by the people of knowledge.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1480 Grade:\u00a0Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0642\u0650\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u064a\u0652\u062b\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31820,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/08\/ibn-abbas-prevalence-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":13531,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Sins: Prevalence of sins, prevalence of divine afflictions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Yahya ibn Sa\u2019id reported: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cAdultery does not become prevalent among people but that there will be much death among them. People do not defraud in weights and measures but that their provision will be cut off. People do not judge by\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6663,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/19\/grand-petty-theft\/","url_meta":{"origin":13531,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Thieves: Cutting the hand applied to grand theft, not petty theft","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The hand of the thief was never cut in the lifetime of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, for what is less than the price of a shield or piece of armor, and both of them were expensive. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6408, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28776,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/07\/pen-lifted-from-three\/","url_meta":{"origin":13531,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Responsibility: The pen is lifted from three people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali ibn Abi Talib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe pen is lifted from three people: a sleeping person until he awakens, a child until he becomes an adult, and an insane person until he regains his sanity.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1423 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6653,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/19\/justice-equal-punishments\/","url_meta":{"origin":13531,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Justice: Legal punishments apply equally in society","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Quraysh had been anxious about a woman who had committed theft and they said, \u201cWho will speak to the Messenger of Allah about her?\u201d Some said, \u201cWho would dare to but Usama, one beloved by the Messenger of Allah?\u201d Thus, Usama spoke to him and the Messenger\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13531","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dail